- frontend use angular 20
- always use modern angular features
- preferably use the angular cli to generate boilerplate code
- always use the angular cli to generate components, services, pipes, directives, guards, interceptors, resolvers
- always use the angular cli to generate e2e tests
- always use the angular cli to generate unit tests
- always use the angular cli to generate integration tests
- always use the angular cli to generate performance tests
- always use the angular cli to generate accessibility tests
- always use the angular cli to generate security tests
- all components should be standalone
- always prefer using the components already made instead of using base html tags
- when creating a service that interacts with the backend, always use the http client
- always have template, scss and typescript in their own respective files
- always write the test files when creating new services or components